---
import BaseLayout from '../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---
<BaseLayout title="Year-End Security Review: Planning for 2027 | Sheepdog" description="Conduct a year-end security review. Assess what worked, what didn't, and plan improvements for next year." showMatrix={true}>
  <section>
    <h1>Year-End Security Review: Planning for 2027</h1>
    <p class="lead">December is the perfect time to reflect on your security program's performance this year and plan improvements for next year. A structured year-end review sets you up for success in 2027.</p>
  </section>

  <section>
    <h2>Year-End Review Objectives</h2>
    <ul>
      <li>Assess security program effectiveness</li>
      <li>Identify lessons from incidents and successes</li>
      <li>Review metrics and KPIs</li>
      <li>Budget planning for next year</li>
      <li>Staffing and resource needs</li>
      <li>Strategic priorities for 2027</li>
    </ul>
  </section>

  <section>
    <h2>Review Process</h2>
    
    <h3>Executive Summary</h3>
    <ul>
      <li>Key security achievements in 2026</li>
      <li>Major incidents and outcomes</li>
      <li>Compliance status</li>
      <li>Budget and ROI</li>
      <li>Overall maturity assessment</li>
    </ul>

    <h3>Incident Analysis</h3>
    <ul>
      <li>Total incidents detected and handled</li>
      <li>Incident categories and trends</li>
      <li>Lessons learned from each major incident</li>
      <li>Time to detect and respond (compare to targets)</li>
      <li>Detection method (internal vs external)</li>
    </ul>

    <h3>Compliance Assessment</h3>
    <ul>
      <li>Audit results (passes, findings, timeframes)</li>
      <li>Regulatory requirements met</li>
      <li>Outstanding compliance items</li>
      <li>Certifications maintained or achieved</li>
    </ul>

    <h3>Control Effectiveness</h3>
    <ul>
      <li>Which controls worked well?</li>
      <li>Which controls need improvement?</li>
      <li>Detection accuracy (false positive rate)</li>
      <li>Response effectiveness</li>
      <li>Enforcement and compliance rates</li>
    </ul>

    <h3>Metrics Review</h3>
    <ul>
      <li>Vulnerability metrics (patch rates, open vulns)</li>
      <li>Security awareness (training completion, phishing clickrate)</li>
      <li>Access control compliance</li>
      <li>MTTR for vulnerability remediation</li>
      <li>Incident response metrics</li>
    </ul>

    <h3>Threat Landscape Changes</h3>
    <ul>
      <li>New threats emerged during 2026?</li>
      <li>Threat actors targeting your industry?</li>
      <li>Techniques and tactics evolution?</li>
      <li>Impact on your security strategy</li>
    </ul>

    <h3>Staff and Skills Assessment</h3>
    <ul>
      <li>Staffing levels vs workload</li>
      <li>Skill gaps identified</li>
      <li>Training investments needed</li>
      <li>Retention and recruitment challenges</li>
      <li>Succession planning needs</li>
    </ul>

    <h3>Technology Assessment</h3>
    <ul>
      <li>Effectiveness of current tools</li>
      <li>Gaps in security technology</li>
      <li>Integration and interoperability issues</li>
      <li>Upgrades or replacements needed</li>
      <li>New technology to evaluate</li>
    </ul>
  </section>

  <section>
    <h2>Planning for 2027</h2>
    
    <h3>Strategic Priorities</h3>
    <ol>
      <li>Top 3-5 security initiatives for next year</li>
      <li>Align with business objectives</li>
      <li>Budget and resource allocation</li>
      <li>Timeline and milestones</li>
      <li>Success measures</li>
    </ol>

    <h3>Budget Planning</h3>
    <ul>
      <li>Personnel costs (salaries, hiring)</li>
      <li>Tools and technology</li>
      <li>Training and certifications</li>
      <li>Professional services (penetration testing, consulting)</li>
      <li>Contingency budget for incidents</li>
    </ul>

    <h3>Staffing Plan</h3>
    <ul>
      <li>Headcount needs</li>
      <li>Skill development priorities</li>
      <li>Certification goals</li>
      <li>Retention strategy</li>
    </ul>

    <h3>Roadmap Development</h3>
    <ul>
      <li><strong>Q1 2027:</strong> Vulnerability management improvements</li>
      <li><strong>Q2 2027:</strong> Incident response enhancement</li>
      <li><strong>Q3 2027:</strong> Detection capability expansion</li>
      <li><strong>Q4 2027:</strong> Continuous improvement</li>
    </ul>
  </section>

  <section>
    <h2>Common Year-End Findings</h2>
    <ul>
      <li>Metrics not properly tracked (start tracking in 2027)</li>
      <li>Incidents still take too long to detect/respond</li>
      <li>Compliance gaps persist (fix before next audit)</li>
      <li>Security training completion low (mandate in 2027)</li>
      <li>Tools not integrated properly (consolidate in 2027)</li>
    </ul>
  </section>

  <section>
    <h2>Communication Plan</h2>
    <ul>
      <li><strong>Board/Executive:</strong> Strategic summary and budget request</li>
      <li><strong>Business Leaders:</strong> How security supports business goals</li>
      <li><strong>Security Team:</strong> Detailed review and planning session</li>
      <li><strong>All Staff:</strong> Highlight security achievements</li>
    </ul>
  </section>

  <section class="cta">
    <h2>Conduct Your Year-End Review</h2>
    <p>Sheepdog Cyber Defense helps organizations conduct comprehensive security program reviews and develop strategic plans for the coming year.</p>
    <a href="/contact" class="btn">Schedule Your Review</a>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>

